.form-group(ng-class="{ error: errors.name }")
	.input-group
		input.form-control.input-lg(type="text", placeholder="Title", ng-model="release.name")
		span.input-group-addon(uib-tooltip="Click for an inspirational random title!", tooltip-placement="right", tooltip-append-to-body="true")
			+icon('bulb').a(ng-click="generateReleaseName()")
	.alert.alert-danger(ng-show="errors.name")
		+icon('warning').shift-up.space-right
		| {{ errors.name }}
	.alert.alert--rounded.alert--aligned(ng-show="showHelp")
		+icon('info')
		p Put something non-technical here.
		p This is what will show up when your release gets listed under the game. It is basically what distinguishes your release from others of the same game. Choose a name that brings across the nature of your virtual table, or click the light bulb until you're happy. ;)
